III. CR-UIT is the name of 3 stringed instrument used of old in Scotland and Ireland, which was the same with the Welch crwdd or crwth. For a long time past it has been confined to North Wales, so that the people of that part of the principality have been accustomed to consider it as be- ing exclusively their own, as we learn from the Rev. Mr- Evan Evans' account of it.
